# Rendered figures from the image-processing notebooks (686 MB). Regenerable by re-running
# the notebook, and git cannot delta-compress PNGs, so every re-run would add megabytes to
# history permanently.
notebooks/1. Qualitative Evaluation/output/
notebooks/2. Data Processing/output/
/output/
thesis_figures/
master_thesis.tex

# notebooks/3. GNN/output/ is deliberately NOT ignored. It holds the GNN experiment logs
# (cv_experiment/, overfit_experiment/) -- TensorBoard event files, the per-fold summary
# CSVs and the prediction graphs. Those are run records: re-running gives a different run,
# not the one you had, so they are irreplaceable rather than regenerable.
#
# They are not cheap. `writer.add_figure` embeds each rendered figure INSIDE the event
# file, so the events are ~53 MB and every CV run adds roughly 15-37 MB permanently. That
# cost is accepted deliberately: these runs were lost once to a stray `rm -rf output`, and
# nothing outside git would have brought them back.

# Notebook outputs are stripped on commit by the nbstripout filter (see .gitattributes),
# not ignored -- they cannot be, since they live inside the tracked .ipynb. They stay in
# your working copy; only the committed version is clean.

# A downloaded third-party example, not our work. It ships with "keep_output": true in its
# metadata, which is nbstripout's opt-out, so the filter honours it and the file stages at
# 42.6 MB -- more than the rest of the repository combined. Not ours to strip or to track.
notebooks/1. Qualitative Evaluation/mono_channel_bact.ipynb

